=== Test 12: Auto-Boxing with Operator Overloading ===
--- Int auto-boxing and operators ---
a = 10
b = 20
a + b = 30
b - a = 10
a * b = 200
b / a = 2
17 % 5 = 2
--- Int comparison operators ---
15 < 25: true
15 <= 15: true
25 > 15: true
25 >= 25: true
15 == 15: true
15 != 25: true
--- Float auto-boxing and operators ---
f1 = 10.5
f2 = 2.5
f1 + f2 = 13
f1 - f2 = 8
f1 * f2 = 26.25
f1 / f2 = 4.2
2.5 < 10.5: true
10.5 == 10.5: true
--- String auto-boxing and operators ---
s1 = Hello
s2 =  World
s1 + s2 = Hello World
Hello == Hello: true
Hello != World: true
--- Bool auto-boxing ---
bool1 = true
bool2 = false
true == true: true
true != false: true
--- Mixed operations ---
(5 + 10) * 15 = 225
15 - (10 / 5) = 13
--- Auto-boxing in function calls ---
add(30, 40) = 70
--- Auto-boxing in arrays ---
Array elements:
numbers[0] = 1
numbers[1] = 2
numbers[2] = 3
numbers[3] = 4
numbers[4] = 5
numbers[0] + numbers[1] = 3
--- Comparison chains ---
10 < 20: true
20 < 30: true
Both comparisons true
--- Negative numbers and edge cases ---
-10 + -5 = -15
-10 * -5 = 50
-5 > -10: true
0 + 0 = 0
0 == 0: true
=== Test 12 Complete ===
